"title": "5009: conscience, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5009",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The faculty, given to every individual, that is capable of producing guilt, or reassurance in the case of innocence. Though never wholly reliable, the conscience is cleansed when the individual turns to God for forgiveness. It is possible for the conscience to become deadened through lack of use.</p>\n<h2>The natural conscience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:14-Rom2:15\">ROM 2:14–2:15</a></strong> <em>Human beings have a built-in ability to know what is right and wrong.</em></p>\n<h2>Guilty consciences</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:21\">GEN 42:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:27\">EXO 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:5\">1SA 24:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:10\">2SA 24:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:6\">EZR 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:12\">PSA 40:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:7-John8:11\">JHN 8:7–8:11</a></p>\n<h2>Clear consciences</h2>\n<h3>Before God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:16\">ACT 24:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job27:6\">JOB 27:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:1\">ACT 23:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:1\">ROM 9:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:3\">2TI 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Before others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:12\">2CO 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:5-Gen20:6\">GEN 20:5–20:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:2\">2CO 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:10\">1TH 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:5\">1TI 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:9\">1TI 3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:18\">HEB 13:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:16\">1PE 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:4\">1CO 4:4</a> <em>Conscience is not an infallible guide and a clear conscience does not necessarily imply innocence before God.</em></p>\n<h2>Consciences cleansed by the death of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:10\">PSA 51:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:9\">HEB 9:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:2\">HEB 10:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:22\">HEB 10:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:21\">1PE 3:21</a></p>\n<h2>Bad or corrupted consciences</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:15-Titus1:16\">TIT 1:15–1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:5\">GEN 6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:14\">EXO 7:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:15\">EXO 8:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:15\">JER 6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:9\">JER 17:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:2\">ACT 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:5\">ROM 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:19\">EPH 4:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:19\">1TI 1:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:2\">1TI 4:2</a></p>",
